parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the timing chain can cause the engine to stall, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded. It can also cause damage to other engine components, resulting in costly repairs.
symptoms: The engine makes a loud whining or rattling noise
and the engine stalls or loses power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the catalytic converter can cause the vehicle to fail emissions tests, leading to costly repairs and potential environmental harm.
symptoms: and the catalytic converter needs to be replaced.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch hydraulic system can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
and the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the high pressure fuel pump can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, and have poor fuel economy, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: and may display error codes P0090 and P0087.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the catalytic converter can cause the vehicle to lose power, have poor fuel economy, and emit excessive pollutants, which can lead to environmental harm and potential health risks.
symptoms: and may display error codes P0420

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel rail pressure sensor can cause the vehicle to have poor fuel economy, lose power, and stall, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle has poor fuel economy

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The inaccurate fuel gauge display can cause the vehicle to run out of gas and stall on the highway, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The fuel gauge display is inaccurate
showing empty when it's not and showing full when it's not.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel line can cause fuel to leak, which can lead to fires, accidents, or environmental harm.
symptoms: Fuel leaks from the fuel line fitting/clamp on the back side of the engine
causing a strong smell of gasoline and forming puddles.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the catalytic converter can cause the "check engine" light to illuminate, leading to expensive repairs and potentially causing damage to other engine components.
symptoms: the vehicle's engine performance is affected
and the catalytic converter needs to be replaced.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the timing chain can cause the engine to lose power, stall, or shut down, leading to a loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: the vehicle is unable to maintain speed
and the timing chain needs to be replaced.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The degradation of the dashboard material can cause the dashboard to crack, melt, or become deformed, affecting the aesthetic appearance of the vehicle and potentially causing distraction while driving.
symptoms: the material becomes brittle or soft
and the dashboard needs to be replaced.
